        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 1 at 10:59PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1059 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Canadian to near Briscoe to 6 miles north
of Lela. Movement was southeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Shamrock, New Mobeetie, Canadian, Twitty, Mobeetie, Allison, Dozier,
Lela, Wheeler, Lake Marvin, Kellerville, and Briscoe.

This includes Interstate 40 between mile markers 145 and 176.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 100 AM CDT for
the Panhandle of Texas.</instruction>
